cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on learning visual concepts, word representations, and semantic parsing of sentences using paired images and questions/answers. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a neuro-symbolic reasoning module, which involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.CL, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.NE.
